          'answer': 'We consider your data to be of utmost importance. The possibility of data loss is orders of magnitude lower than that of even a RAID Array, because to lose data, not only is a simultaneous failure of 3 drives needed (an extremely rare occurance where a RAID Array would lose data), it would need to be the 3 drives that store the same chunks of data as each other, across 3 physically separate servers.'
